    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Exercices Semaine 9\"\nformat:\n  html:\n    html-math-method: mathjax\n    include-after-body: include/webex_2.js\n    css: include/webex_2.css\ntoc: false\neditor: source\n---\n\n\n\n\n\n<!-- JavaScript for legacy hint/explanation buttons -->\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\nfunction toggleAlertLegacy(alertId, message, type) {\n  var alertBox = document.getElementById(alertId);\n  if (!alertBox) return;\n\n  var alertsContainer = alertBox.closest('.question-alerts');\n  if (alertsContainer) {\n    var allAlerts = alertsContainer.querySelectorAll('.alert');\n    allAlerts.forEach(function(alert) {\n      if (alert.id !== alertId) {\n        alert.style.display = \"none\";\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  var alertMessage = alertBox.querySelector(\".alertMessage\");\n  var alertType = alertBox.querySelector(\".alertType\");\n\n  if (alertBox.style.display === \"block\") {\n    alertBox.style.display = \"none\";\n  } else {\n    alertMessage.innerHTML = message;\n    alertType.innerHTML = (type === 'hint') ? '&#10067; Indice' : '&#128161; Explication';\n\n    var isDark = document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-theme') === 'dark';\n    alertBox.style.backgroundColor = (type === 'hint')\n      ? (isDark ? '#3a3520' : '#FFEDA3')\n      : (isDark ? '#1a3a2a' : '#C0EDC2');\n    alertBox.style.borderColor = (type === 'hint')\n      ? (isDark ? '#d69e2e' : '#E5B800')\n      : (isDark ? '#68d391' : '#388E3C');\n    alertBox.style.color = isDark ? '#e2e8f0' : '#1a202c';\n    alertBox.style.display = \"block\";\n\n    MathJax.typesetPromise([alertMessage]);\n  }\n}\n</script>\n\n<!-- CSS for AI Help button and alerts container -->\n<style>\n.custom-button.ai-help {\n  background: #E8E0F0;\n  border: 2px solid #5a3d8a;\n}\n\n.custom-button.ai-help:hover {\n  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #5a67d8 0%, #9f7aea 100%);\n  border-color: transparent;\n  color: white;\n  transform: scale(1.05);\n}\n\n[data-theme=\"dark\"] .custom-button.ai-help {\n  background: #2d2440;\n  border-color: #7c6aad;\n  color: #e2e8f0;\n}\n\n[data-theme=\"dark\"] .custom-button.ai-help:hover {\n  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #5a67d8 0%, #9f7aea 100%);\n  border-color: transparent;\n  color: white;\n}\n\n.question-alerts {\n  margin-top: 8px;\n}\n\n.question-alerts .alert {\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\n}\n</style>\n\n<!-- MathJax for Rendering Math -->\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" async\n  src=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/3.2.2/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js\">\n</script>\n\n\n---\n\n## Question 1\n\nLes scores d'un examen de physique sont distribués normalement avec une espérance de \\\\(80\\\\) et un écart-type de \\\\(5\\\\). Si nous sélectionnons aléatoirement \\\\(20\\\\) étudiants de la classe, leur score moyen est de \\\\(75\\\\). Laquelle de ces propositions est correcte?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_KPEBLVNBYE'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_KPEBLVNBYE\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(80\\\\) et \\\\(5\\\\) sont des paramètres. \\\\(75\\\\) est une statistique</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_KPEBLVNBYE\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(80\\\\) et \\\\(5\\\\) sont des statistiques, \\\\(75\\\\) est un paramètre</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_KPEBLVNBYE\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(80\\\\) et \\\\(75\\\\) sont des statistiques, \\\\(5\\\\) est un paramètre</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_KPEBLVNBYE\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(5\\\\) et \\\\(75\\\\) sont des statistiques, \\\\(80\\\\) est un paramètre</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q1-hint', 'Relisez la notion de statistique et de paramètres dans les slides de la semaine \\\\(8\\\\).', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q1-expl', '\\\\(80\\\\) et \\\\(5\\\\) sont respectivement l\\'espérance et l\\'écart type de la distribution des scores et sont donc des paramètres. \\\\(75\\\\) est la moyenne empirique (aussi notée \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\)) de l\\'échantillon et est ainsi une statistique', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q1-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q1-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 2\n\nSi la taille de l'échantillon \\\\(n\\\\) augmente, quelle affirmation est correcte à propos de \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\), l'estimateur de l'espérance \\\\(\\\\mu\\\\)?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_AFNRGNMFOQ'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_AFNRGNMFOQ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>L&apos;estimateur \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) devient plus variable</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_AFNRGNMFOQ\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>L&apos;estimateur \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\)  devient moins variable</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_AFNRGNMFOQ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>L&apos;estimateur \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) devient plus grand</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_AFNRGNMFOQ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>L&apos;estimateur \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) devient plus petit</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_AFNRGNMFOQ\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>La variance de l&apos;estimateur \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) n&apos;est pas affectée</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q2-hint', 'Quelle est la variance de \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\)?', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q2-expl', 'Si la taille de l\\'échantillon \\\\(n\\\\) augmente, la variance de l\\'estimateur \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\), donnée par \\\\(\\\\text{Var}(\\\\bar{X}) = \\\\frac{\\\\sigma^2}{n}\\\\), diminue. Cela signifie que \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) devient plus précis (moins variable) car les valeurs de \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) sont plus concentrées autour de la vraie valeur de l\\'espérance \\\\(\\\\mu\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q2-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q2-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 3\n\nOn considère une variable aléatoire \\\\(X\\\\) distribuée normalement avec une espérance \\\\(\\\\mu = 50\\\\) et une variance \\\\(\\\\sigma^2 = 25\\\\). On considère un échantillon de taille \\\\(n = 100\\\\). Quelle est la variance de \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\), la moyenne de l'échantillon ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_FZCRDNDSBN'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_FZCRDNDSBN\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.75\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_FZCRDNDSBN\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(2.5\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_FZCRDNDSBN\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(25\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_FZCRDNDSBN\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.25\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_FZCRDNDSBN\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(100\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q3-hint', 'Quelle est la formule de la variance de \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\)?', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q3-expl', 'La variance de \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) est donnée par \\\\(\\\\text{Var}(\\\\bar{X}) = \\\\frac{\\\\sigma^2}{n}\\\\). Dans ce cas, \\\\(\\\\sigma^2 = 25\\\\) et \\\\(n = 100\\\\), donc \\\\(\\\\text{Var}(\\\\bar{X}) = \\\\frac{25}{100} = 0.25\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q3-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q3-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 4\n\nOn considère une variable aléatoire \\\\(X\\\\) distribuée normalement avec une espérance \\\\(\\\\mu = 50\\\\) et une variance \\\\(\\\\sigma^2 = 25\\\\). Maintenant, on considère un échantillon de taille \\\\(n = 100\\\\). Quelle est la probabilité que la moyenne de l'échantillon \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) soit supérieure à 51 ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_JBFORXFQMS'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JBFORXFQMS\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.1587\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JBFORXFQMS\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.0228\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JBFORXFQMS\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.3085\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JBFORXFQMS\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.5\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_JBFORXFQMS\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.8413\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q4-hint', 'Utilisez la distribution normale de \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) et calculez la probabilité en standardisant la variable.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q4-expl', 'La moyenne de l\\'échantillon \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) suit une distribution normale avec une espérance \\\\(\\\\mu = 50\\\\) et une variance \\\\(\\\\text{Var}(\\\\bar{X}) = \\\\frac{\\\\sigma^2}{n} = \\\\frac{25}{100} = 0.25\\\\). L\\'écart-type de \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) est donc \\\\(\\\\sqrt{0.25} = 0.5\\\\). La probabilité que \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) soit supérieure à 51 est donnée par \\\\(P(\\\\bar{X} > 51) = P\\\\left(Z > \\\\frac{51 - 50}{0.5}\\\\right) = P(Z > 2) = 1- \\\\Phi(2) \\\\approx 0.0228\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q4-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q4-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 5\n\nOn considère une variable aléatoire \\\\(X\\\\) distribuée normalement avec une espérance \\\\(\\\\mu = 100\\\\) et une variance \\\\(\\\\sigma^2 = 16\\\\). Maintenant, on considère un échantillon de taille \\\\(n = 64\\\\). Quelle est la probabilité que la moyenne de l'échantillon \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) soit inférieure à 99 ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_XWFBGVDCJH'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XWFBGVDCJH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.0478\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XWFBGVDCJH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.1587\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XWFBGVDCJH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.3085\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XWFBGVDCJH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.5\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XWFBGVDCJH\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.0228\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XWFBGVDCJH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.1237\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q5-hint', 'Utilisez la distribution normale de \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) et calculez la probabilité en standardisant la variable.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q5-expl', 'La moyenne de l\\'échantillon \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) suit une distribution normale avec une espérance \\\\(\\\\mu = 100\\\\) et une variance \\\\(\\\\text{Var}(\\\\bar{X}) = \\\\frac{\\\\sigma^2}{n} = \\\\frac{16}{64} = 0.25\\\\). L\\'écart-type de \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) est donc \\\\(\\\\sqrt{0.25} = 0.5\\\\). La probabilité que \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) soit inférieure à \\\\(99\\\\) est donnée par \\\\(P(\\\\bar{X} < 99) = P\\\\left(Z < \\\\frac{99 - 100}{0.5}\\\\right) = P(Z < -2) = 0.0228\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q5-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q5-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 6\n\nOn considère l'échantillon suivant: \\\\(\\\\{1.5, 2.6, 3.9, 5.4,7.2, 8.35\\\\}\\\\). Calculez la moyenne \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) et l'écart type \\\\(s\\\\) de cet ensemble de données.\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_BTJVHEBEWH'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_BTJVHEBEWH\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\bar{X} = 4.825, s \\\\approx 2.66 \\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_BTJVHEBEWH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\bar{X} = 2.825, s \\\\approx 4.66 \\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_BTJVHEBEWH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\bar{X} = 10.925, s \\\\approx 3.56 \\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_BTJVHEBEWH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\bar{X} = 1.525, s \\\\approx 2.21 \\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q6-hint', 'Calculez \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) et \\\\(s\\\\) à l\\'aide de leur définition.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q6-expl', 'Pour calculer la moyenne \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\), nous additionnons toutes les valeurs de l\\'échantillon \\\\(\\\\{1.5, 2.6, 3.9, 5.4,7.2, 8.35\\\\}\\\\) et les divisons par le nombre total de valeurs, soit \\\\(6\\\\), ce qui donne \\\\(\\\\bar{X} = \\\\frac{28.95}{6} = 4.825\\\\). Pour l\\'écart type \\\\(s\\\\), nous calculons d\\'abord la somme des carrés des écarts entre chaque valeur et la moyenne, soit \\\\((1.5 - 4.825)^2 + (2.6 - 4.825)^2 + \\\\ldots + (8.35 - 4.825)^2 = 35.25875\\\\), puis nous divisons cette somme par \\\\(n-1 = 5\\\\) et prenons la racine carrée du résultat, ce qui donne \\\\(s = \\\\sqrt{\\\\frac{35.25875}{5}} = 2.655513 \\\\approx 2.656\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q6-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q6-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 7\n\nEn utilisant la moyenne \\\\(\\\\bar{X}\\\\) et l'écart type \\\\(s\\\\) que vous avez calculés dans l'exercice précédent, déterminez l'erreur standard de la moyenne \\\\(\\\\frac{s}{\\\\sqrt{n}}\\\\) pour l'échantillon \\\\(\\\\{1.5, 2.6, 3.9, 5.4,7.2, 8.35\\\\}\\\\).\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_NFBQRVHTDH'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_NFBQRVHTDH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(e.s.(\\\\bar{X}) = \\\\frac{s}{\\\\sqrt{n}} = 0.0478\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_NFBQRVHTDH\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(e.s.(\\\\bar{X}) = \\\\frac{s}{\\\\sqrt{n}} = 1.084109\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_NFBQRVHTDH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(e.s.(\\\\bar{X}) = \\\\frac{s}{\\\\sqrt{n}} = 2.05219\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_NFBQRVHTDH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(e.s.(\\\\bar{X}) = \\\\frac{s}{\\\\sqrt{n}} = 3.12643\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q7-hint', 'Calculez \\\\(e.s.(\\\\bar{X})\\\\) à l\\'aide de sa définition.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q7-expl', '\\\\(e.s.(\\\\bar{X}) = \\\\frac{s}{\\\\sqrt{n}} = \\\\frac{2.655513}{\\\\sqrt{6}} =  1.084109\\\\)', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q7-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q7-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n---\n\n**Tir à 3 points de Stephen Curry**\n\nOn a les données suivantes sur les réussites au tir à trois points de Stephen Curry (données réelles avril 2025) :\n\n| Date             | Adversaire             | Tentatives à 3 points  | Réussites à 3 points |\n|------------------|------------------------|------------------------|-----------------------|\n| 1er avril 2025   | Memphis Grizzlies    | 20                     | 12                    |\n| 3 avril 2025     | Los Angeles Lakers   | 11                     | 4                     |\n| 4 avril 2025     | Denver Nuggets      | 15                     | 7                     |\n| 6 avril 2025     | Houston Rockets     | 8                      | 1                     |\n\n\n## Question 8\n\nBasé sur ces données, quelle est la proportion de réussites à 3 points de Stephen Curry ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_XALMOVQJCY'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XALMOVQJCY\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.3790\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XALMOVQJCY\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.4444\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XALMOVQJCY\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.3890\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_XALMOVQJCY\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(24\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q8-hint', 'Calculez \\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\) à l\\'aide de sa définition.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q8-expl', 'Ici on a \\\\(X=24\\\\) paniers à trois points réussis pour \\\\(n=54\\\\) tentatives, soit une propotion de \\\\(\\\\hat{p}=X/n\\\\approx0.4444\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q8-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q8-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n## Question 9\n\nBasé sur ces données, quelle est l\\'erreur standard de la proportion de réussites à 3 points de Stephen Curry ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_ARBHAIAHPB'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_ARBHAIAHPB\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.0046\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_ARBHAIAHPB\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.4969\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_ARBHAIAHPB\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.0676\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_ARBHAIAHPB\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(0.0663\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q9-hint', 'Calculez \\\\(e.s.(\\\\hat{p})\\\\) à l\\'aide de sa définition.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q9-expl', 'Ici on a \\\\(\\\\hat{p}=0.4444\\\\) (Question 8) et \\\\(n=54\\\\), donc \\\\(e.s.(\\\\hat{p})=\\\\sqrt{\\\\hat{p}(1-\\\\hat{p})/n}\\\\approx0.0676\\\\).', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q9-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q9-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n## Question 10\n\nQuelle affirmation est correcte à propose du Théorème Centrale Limite (TCL) dans ce cas ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_WSGIIJQTWH'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_WSGIIJQTWH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>Le TCL s&apos;applique car les pourcentages proviennent d&apos;un joueur professionnel, donc ils suivent une loi normale.</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_WSGIIJQTWH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>Le TCL ne peut pas s&apos;appliquer ici car les tirs à 3 points ne suivent pas une loi normale.</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_WSGIIJQTWH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>Le TCL s&apos;applique dès qu&apos;on connaît la moyenne et la variance des taux de réussite, quelle que soit la taille de l&apos;échantillon.</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_WSGIIJQTWH\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>Le TCL s&apos;applique car l&apos;échantillon est suffisamment grand pour justifier l&apos;approximation normale.</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_WSGIIJQTWH\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>Le TCL permet de conclure que la proportion est égale à la probabilité de réussite à 3 points.</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q10-hint', 'Revoir les conditions d\\'application du TCL dans les slides.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q10-expl', 'Ici on a \\\\(n=54\\\\). Bien que \\\\(p\\\\) (le paramètre) ne soit pas connu,on a \\\\(n\\\\hat{p}=24>10\\\\) et \\\\(n(1-\\\\hat{p}=30>10\\\\) qui sont les deux indications que la taille d\\'échantillon est suffisamment grande. Les autres affirmations sont clairement fausses.', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q10-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q10-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n## Question 11\n\nSupposez que chaque tir à trois points de Stephen Curry ait une probabilité de succès de \\\\(p=0.397\\\\). En supposant que le TCL s'applique, quelle est la distribution approximative de \\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\) ?\n\n<div class='webex-radiogroup' id='radio_WZFSGROIIY'><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_WZFSGROIIY\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\sim\\\\mathcal{N}(0.4444, 0.0676^2)\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_WZFSGROIIY\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\sim\\\\text{Bin}(54, 0.397)\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_WZFSGROIIY\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\sim\\\\mathcal{N}(0.397, 0.397^2)\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_WZFSGROIIY\" value=\"\" data-feedback=\"Faux\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\sim\\\\mathcal{U}(0, 1)\\\\)</span></label><label><input type=\"radio\" autocomplete=\"off\" name=\"radio_WZFSGROIIY\" value=\"answer\" data-feedback=\"Vrai\"></input> <span>\\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\sim\\\\mathcal{N}(0.397, 0.0666^2)\\\\)</span></label><div class='webex-feedback-box'></div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"question-buttons\">\n<button class=\"custom-button hint\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q11-hint', 'Revoir l\\'approximation donnée par le TCL dans les slides.', 'hint')\">&#10067; Indice</button>\n<button class=\"custom-button explanation\" onclick=\"toggleAlertLegacy('q11-expl', 'Par hypothèse on a \\\\(p=0.397\\\\). Ici on \\\\(n=54\\\\). Donc on déduit que \\\\(\\\\sqrt{p(1-p)/n}\\\\approx0.0666\\\\). On conclut que \\\\(\\\\hat{p}\\\\sim\\\\mathcal{N}(0.397, 0.0666^2)\\\\) grâce au TCL.', 'explanation')\">&#128161; Explication</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"question-alerts\">\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q11-hint\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" id=\"q11-expl\" style=\"display: none;\">\n  <strong class=\"alertType\"></strong>: <span class=\"alertMessage\"></spa